{
  "stem": "21308.3",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We went back in 1944 after D-Day.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Very briefly, after Dunkirk and after the collapse of France and after France gave in and started collaborating with the Germans, it was patently clear that the old British Empire was on its own as far as the field was concerned.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And although many Frenchmen were evacuated from Dunkirk along with the British, they-- most of them opted to go back to France and in fact, they were conveyed back to France on British transports under the orders of Winston Churchill.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Now, I must make it clear that it wasn't the United Kingdom that stood alone, as is so often said.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was the British Commonwealth of Nations.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they were supported.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Because of the link between President Roosevelt of the States and Winston Churchill, we were given a lot of material help, which I might say we had to pay for.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was cash and carry.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And when the cash ran out, President Roosevelt thought up the wonderful idea of lease-lend.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And then, of course, once the Japs attacked Pearl Harbor, they were in it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But I must make the point that at no time was the United Kingdom on its own.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It was the British Commonwealth of Nations.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Now, after Dunkirk, the army had to be rebuilt.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "The army came back from Dunkirk without any weapons, without any transport, and with such stuff as they could carry.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And that wasn't very much.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So we had to requip, we had to completely retrain.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Commanders who failed in France was sacked, new ones had to be found.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And in fact, I was mixed up in all that because I went to join a regiment which had never had any guns.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
